				</div>
			</slide>
			<slide id="api-value">
				<title>API Value Propositions</title>
				<ol>
					<li>Increase <em>flexibility</em> by allowing capabilities to be added/changed more easily</li>
					<li>Improve <em>innovation</em> by improving reuse and allowing more economical experimentation</li>
					<li>Increase <em>scalability</em> by allowing capabilities to be scaled individually</li>
				</ol>
			</slide>
		</part>
		<part id="api-technology">
			<title>API Technology</title>
			<slide id="api-styles">
				<title>API Styles</title>
				<ul>
					<li>APIs support conversations between interacting peers</li>
					<ul>
						<li>Some conversations are point-to-point</li>
						<li>Some conversations are point-to-multipoint</li>
						<li>Some conversations are point-to-ether</li>
					</ul>
					<li>Different API styles support different conversation styles</li>
					<ul>
						<li><em>Tunnel Style:</em> XML-RPC, SOAP, gRPC, Avro</li>
						<li><em>URI Style:</em> OpenAPI/Swagger, RAML, API Blueprint</li>
						<li><em>Hypermedia Style:</em> HAL, Siren, Atom, HATEOAS</li>
						<li><em>Query Style:</em> GraphQL, OData, SPARQL</li>
						<li><em>Event Style:</em> MQ, WebSub, MQTT, XMPP, AMQP, Kafka</li>
					</ul>
				</ul>
			</slide>
